To convert the above markdown formatted text to html, we can use the following C++ function:

std::string convert_markdown_to_html(const std::string& markdown_text) {
    std::string html_text;

    // Replace the markdown header symbol (#) with the corresponding html header symbol (<h1>)
    html_text = markdown_text.replace("#", "<h1>");

    // Replace the markdown list symbol (-) with the corresponding html list symbol (<li>)
    for (char& c : markdown_text) {
        if (c == '-') {
            c = '<li>';
        }
    }

    html_text = "<ul>" + markdown_text + "</ul>";

    return html_text;
}

In this function, we first replace the markdown header symbol (#) with the corresponding html header symbol (<h1>). Then, we replace the markdown list symbol (-) with the corresponding html list symbol (<li>). Finally, we wrap the modified markdown text in an html unordered list (<ul>) to create the final html formatted text.

